text.tspan: Share of population living in extreme poverty vs. mean income or
Extreme poverty is defined as living below the International Poverty Line of 2.15 international-$ per day. This data is adjusted for
inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Data source: World Bank Poverty and Inequality Platform
Note: This data is measured in international-$ at 2017 prices. Depending on the country and year, it relates to either disposable income or
